WEBVTT

00:13.847 --> 00:17.350
In my experience, once you talk to
people, they usually open up pretty

00:17.434 --> 00:18.268
quickly.

00:18.351 --> 00:21.271
People are always telling me that I seem
intimidating.

00:24.983 --> 00:27.610
I'm not very good at approaching
people on my own.

00:27.694 --> 00:30.196
Nice to find someone who shares
my love of manga!

00:33.491 --> 00:36.911
I had always been kinda bored
here since I hadn't found others I had

00:36.995 --> 00:37.996
much in common with.

00:41.291 --> 00:42.167
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:42.250 --> 00:43.084
Thank you.

00:43.168 --> 00:44.002
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:44.085 --> 00:44.919
Thank you.

00:45.003 --> 00:46.129
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:46.212 --> 00:47.422
- Thank you.
- No problem.

00:49.466 --> 00:53.344
What if the only reason someone felt
alone was because no one had found...

00:54.554 --> 00:55.597
The right key?

00:57.557 --> 00:59.642
- HAMBURGER BOM BOM
- And then that guy was like...

00:59.726 --> 01:01.811
Hey, Amamiya, are you even listening?

01:02.687 --> 01:04.439
Hm? Yeah, course I am!

01:05.482 --> 01:06.524
No, I'm not.

02:32.402 --> 02:34.737
THE RAMPARTS OF ICE

02:38.575 --> 02:40.577
EPISODE 2 LOCKSMITH

02:43.496 --> 02:45.206
Now come on, let's go have some fun.

02:45.290 --> 02:46.666
I'm not going anywhere!

02:46.749 --> 02:48.668
Oh, what should I do?

02:50.170 --> 02:51.004
And frustrated.

02:52.380 --> 02:53.715
- And pissed off.
- Come on.

02:54.382 --> 02:56.050
- It'll be super fun!
- I told you...

02:56.676 --> 02:57.844
I'm not going anywhere!

02:58.970 --> 03:00.430
Leave me alone.

03:00.513 --> 03:01.681
Seriously.

03:04.809 --> 03:05.643
Bye.

03:08.479 --> 03:09.856
Sorry. Are you okay?

03:10.565 --> 03:12.817
Oh! I knew it! It was you.

03:14.485 --> 03:15.695
Mr. Giraffe.

03:17.363 --> 03:19.532
Sorry I ignored you, but I couldn't see
you.

03:19.616 --> 03:20.450
Oh, um, well...

03:21.826 --> 03:23.828
- Hm?
- Please pretend to be my friend.

03:24.537 --> 03:25.371
I'm sorry.

03:25.455 --> 03:28.708
Please just stay with me until these
two guys leave me alone.

03:29.459 --> 03:30.293
Huh?

03:30.835 --> 03:32.962
SWIFT

03:33.046 --> 03:35.757
Okay, well, I found my friend, so
I'm fine now. Bye.

03:35.840 --> 03:37.050
Huh? What? What? Huh?

03:37.133 --> 03:39.385
BLURRY

03:40.303 --> 03:41.679
Does she know these guys?

03:42.222 --> 03:44.057
- Stare...
- I guess not.

03:45.975 --> 03:48.144
HURRY

03:48.228 --> 03:50.146
High schoolers these days are such
freaks.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.064
Right?

03:52.732 --> 03:54.025
Thank you very much.

03:55.235 --> 03:57.487
Huh? But I didn't do anything, did I?

03:58.238 --> 04:00.031
Wait, didn't you know them?

04:01.616 --> 04:03.493
They came up and started talking to me.

04:03.576 --> 04:05.245
Wow, you're so popular!

04:06.829 --> 04:07.789
It's not like that!

04:08.706 --> 04:12.293
Uh. Or at least, um, I mean, back there...

04:12.794 --> 04:14.587
This wasn't like that.

04:15.755 --> 04:19.759
They were the kind of guys who only cared
about their own enjoyment, not mine.

04:21.010 --> 04:22.553
They talked down to me.

04:23.388 --> 04:25.390
I-I'm not interested in guys like that.

04:26.516 --> 04:27.350
Or...

04:29.018 --> 04:29.852
Oh.

04:29.936 --> 04:32.063
Agh, why am I blabbering at him
like this?

04:33.022 --> 04:34.941
Oh man, I'm totally oversharing.

04:36.526 --> 04:37.735
I'm gonna weird him out.

04:38.361 --> 04:39.195
Hmm.

04:40.113 --> 04:43.157
So wait, are you saying I should've
knocked their lights out?

04:43.241 --> 04:44.075
What?

04:44.158 --> 04:46.119
Oh, n-n-no, you don't have to go
that far.

04:46.202 --> 04:47.078
Are you sure?

04:48.288 --> 04:49.122
And I'm sorry.

04:49.205 --> 04:52.375
I feel bad.
I kind of used you to get away from them.

04:52.875 --> 04:55.295
Huh? What? Why? It's totally fine.

04:55.962 --> 04:58.089
That's not the kind of thing that
would upset me.

04:58.172 --> 04:59.007
You're good.

05:01.384 --> 05:03.052
Do you live around here, Himuro?

05:03.636 --> 05:05.763
No, I was heading to the community
center.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.682
Huh? Hey, that's where I'm going!

05:08.391 --> 05:10.101
Do you wanna walk there together?

05:13.229 --> 05:14.063
Mm-hm.

05:20.445 --> 05:23.323
Since there are no club activities
during the exam preparation period, your

05:23.406 --> 05:24.824
daily routine tends to get disrupted.

05:24.907 --> 05:26.659
Oh, homeroom is going way over!

05:26.743 --> 05:28.244
Koyun, I'm so sorry to keep you waiting!

05:28.328 --> 05:29.537
Set up a study schedule.

05:31.289 --> 05:32.165
So... uh...

05:33.416 --> 05:34.250
Hm?

05:37.045 --> 05:39.380
Can you, uh, tell me your name, please?

05:40.381 --> 05:42.759
Oh, right. I guess I never actually
introduced myself, did I?

05:42.842 --> 05:43.718
Sorry about that.

05:45.053 --> 05:47.096
Yota. Just call me Yota.

05:48.181 --> 05:50.224
I can't just call him by his first name!

05:51.059 --> 05:52.352
Nice to meet you, Himuro.

05:53.019 --> 05:54.896
Oh. Well, um...

05:55.480 --> 05:58.608
My name... isn't Himuro, it's Hikawa.

05:58.691 --> 06:00.026
What? I'm so sorry!

06:00.526 --> 06:02.362
I wish you would've told me sooner.

06:07.033 --> 06:09.494
So... how far are we from the community
center?

06:09.994 --> 06:11.704
I'm directionally challenged.

06:12.246 --> 06:14.248
About five more minutes and we're there.

06:15.083 --> 06:15.917
Five minutes.

06:17.126 --> 06:19.128
Can we keep this conversation going?

06:24.675 --> 06:27.303
So, Hikawa... Are you and Miki close?

06:28.262 --> 06:29.680
Oh. Well, um...

06:30.390 --> 06:31.265
We're old friends.

06:31.349 --> 06:33.851
We went to the same elementary and
middle schools.

06:34.477 --> 06:35.686
Huh. That's really cool.

06:40.441 --> 06:41.609
Uh.

06:42.485 --> 06:43.611
Since junior high...

06:44.153 --> 06:47.156
So does that mean he's seen what she's
really like, then?

06:47.240 --> 06:48.574
Modern Miki!

06:49.117 --> 06:53.287
You know, to be honest, I thought Miki
was way better the way she used to be!

06:53.788 --> 06:54.872
I think so too.

06:55.373 --> 06:56.249
Oh, good.

06:56.332 --> 06:58.960
It bugs me.
I wanna shout it from the rooftops.

06:59.043 --> 07:01.212
It just feels like such a waste, y'know?

07:01.295 --> 07:02.296
Mm.

07:09.679 --> 07:11.264
- [Cracking up} Hold up.
- HAMBURGER BOM BOM

07:11.347 --> 07:12.598
Seriously?

07:13.766 --> 07:15.059
Wait, is that Yota?

07:15.143 --> 07:16.060
Hm?

07:16.727 --> 07:17.770
Oh yeah, you're right.

07:17.854 --> 07:20.022
No way... The girl next to him is...

07:22.066 --> 07:22.900
Huh?

07:23.693 --> 07:25.653
MEITEN COMMUNITY CENTER

07:25.736 --> 07:26.654
Uh.

07:28.072 --> 07:28.990
- Shh.
- Shh.

07:29.949 --> 07:31.367
Here, we saved you a seat.

07:31.451 --> 07:32.285
Oh. Thanks.

07:32.785 --> 07:33.953
But I don't understand.

07:34.036 --> 07:35.913
What're you both doing here together?

07:37.039 --> 07:39.125
- Together?
- Good question.

07:42.545 --> 07:43.379
Well?

07:44.046 --> 07:45.465
Still waiting for an answer.

07:45.548 --> 07:46.466
Quiet.

07:46.549 --> 07:48.759
Uh. What're you...

07:49.844 --> 07:51.345
Oh! I'm so sorry.

07:53.890 --> 07:54.891
This came out of nowhere!

07:54.974 --> 07:58.936
You guys should've warned me beforehand
instead of just springing it on me like

07:59.020 --> 08:01.105
- that!
- I actually told her not to text you.

08:01.189 --> 08:02.607
So then it'd be a surprise.

08:02.690 --> 08:03.566
Really, Koyun?

08:03.649 --> 08:05.776
Can't believe you played along with him!

08:06.819 --> 08:08.988
Anyway, did you punch the guys who
were messing with her?

08:09.071 --> 08:11.782
- Did you knock their lights out?
- No.

08:11.866 --> 08:13.326
Hikawa said I didn't have to.

08:13.868 --> 08:15.703
I told him it really wasn't necessary.

08:15.786 --> 08:16.787
Lame!

08:18.331 --> 08:19.957
Are you two taking the same train?

08:20.041 --> 08:21.375
I'll walk you to the station.

08:21.459 --> 08:22.418
Aw, thank you!

08:24.253 --> 08:26.464
Yota, do you always go to that
study room?

08:26.547 --> 08:28.090
Uh, yeah, actually.

08:28.841 --> 08:32.261
My younger brother and sister are
still little, so it can get pretty

08:32.345 --> 08:33.179
noisy at home.

08:33.262 --> 08:35.181
Mmm-hmm! What age?

08:35.681 --> 08:38.267
Oh, my brother and sister are both
three years old.

08:38.351 --> 08:41.312
- They're fraternal twins.
- Wow, that's quite an age gap.

08:42.021 --> 08:45.858
So, part of it's to get away from the
noise at home, but, in general, I just

08:45.942 --> 08:48.444
- concentrate way better at the center.
- Oh, I get that.

08:48.528 --> 08:50.738
I didn't scroll on my phone even one
time.

08:50.821 --> 08:52.114
I'm very proud of myself.

08:52.615 --> 08:53.991
That's not that hard.

08:55.660 --> 08:57.119
- Oh.
- Huh?

08:57.203 --> 08:58.037
Hold on a sec.

08:58.788 --> 09:00.164
All that studying...

09:00.248 --> 09:02.667
Gotta replenish my energy with
some sugar.

09:02.750 --> 09:04.627
Ooh, good idea!

09:05.920 --> 09:07.171
I think I'll get one too.

09:12.176 --> 09:14.095
He's taller than the vending machine.

09:14.178 --> 09:15.179
Must be nice.

09:16.973 --> 09:18.641
I wish I had been born that tall.

09:19.850 --> 09:21.227
Go ahead, pick what you want.

09:21.310 --> 09:22.228
Oh, are you sure?

09:22.853 --> 09:24.355
Sweet red bean soup, right?

09:25.064 --> 09:26.357
You know me so well!

09:26.440 --> 09:27.733
This was nice of you, Yota.

09:27.817 --> 09:30.152
I'll make sure to get yours the
next time.

09:30.653 --> 09:31.612
Whoa! Ah, what happened?!

09:31.696 --> 09:33.322
Whoa! Oh! Ay, ay, ay, ay, ay...

09:33.406 --> 09:34.740
FLUSTER

09:34.824 --> 09:37.743
Why'd you have a zillion coins instead of
just using bills?!

09:37.827 --> 09:39.370
- I know, sorry.
- Oh, jeez.

09:39.453 --> 09:42.582
NATURAL SPARKLING LEMON WATER
REFRESHING AND DELICIOUS APPLE JUICE

09:42.665 --> 09:43.666
- Want a drink?
- Huh?

09:43.749 --> 09:45.209
- What about you, Hikawa?
- Me?

09:45.293 --> 09:46.168
Oh, no, uh, I- I...

09:46.252 --> 09:47.086
- Hm.
- Hm.

09:47.670 --> 09:49.839
Well, Miki will just have to pick
for you.

09:49.922 --> 09:51.132
You got it.

09:52.008 --> 09:54.427
COCOA, SWEET RED BEAN SOUP,
AMAZAKE CORN POTAGE

09:54.510 --> 09:56.929
But I want the sweet red bean soup,
so she'll get the sweet red

09:57.013 --> 09:57.847
Hmm, I think she wants the corn
potage soup.

09:57.930 --> 09:59.265
But I want the sweet red bean soup,
so she'll get the sweet red

09:59.348 --> 10:00.182
Seriously?

10:00.266 --> 10:03.477
Well, I want us to drink the
same thing so we can talk about how

10:03.561 --> 10:04.645
delicious it is!

10:05.771 --> 10:06.814
So self-centered.

10:08.024 --> 10:09.066
They seem so close.

10:13.237 --> 10:16.907
I know I mentioned this earlier, but
we went to the same cram school back

10:16.991 --> 10:17.825
in junior high.

10:17.908 --> 10:20.870
So me, Miki, and Minato used to hang out
all the time.

10:20.953 --> 10:24.540
Yup. After cram school, we'd always get
something to eat and just talk.

10:24.624 --> 10:27.376
Mina-
Oh, wait, you're talking about Amamiya?

10:27.460 --> 10:29.629
Whoa! Koyun, I had no idea you knew him!

10:30.671 --> 10:32.548
Well, I wouldn't say I know him.

10:33.174 --> 10:34.759
STRETCH

10:35.635 --> 10:37.637
Oh no, was he bullying you again?

10:37.720 --> 10:38.846
Again?

10:39.639 --> 10:40.514
Uh, well, no, he...

10:41.432 --> 10:42.683
I'm sorry about him.

10:43.392 --> 10:44.977
I swear, you can just ignore him.

10:45.061 --> 10:46.062
What?

10:46.145 --> 10:48.773
Have you and Amamiya had a falling out
or something?

10:49.649 --> 10:50.983
No, I'm just kidding.

10:53.194 --> 10:55.363
Koyun, Yota, and Minato...

10:56.197 --> 10:59.408
So, tell me, Hikawa, does everybody
around you call you Koyun?

11:01.452 --> 11:02.995
- Mm?
- Koyun!

11:03.079 --> 11:05.581
- Uh, yes?
- It's a pretty good nickname!

11:06.290 --> 11:08.584
- Yeah, right?
- Don't let it get to your head.

11:09.752 --> 11:12.505
I know I said it before, but just call me
Yota.

11:12.588 --> 11:15.049
I don't like to make things super
complicated.

11:15.132 --> 11:15.966
Or too formal.

11:16.050 --> 11:17.468
- Uh...
- Oh, I feel you.

11:17.551 --> 11:20.596
I prefer Miki to some dumb little
nickname.

11:21.305 --> 11:22.723
Hmm, is that so?

11:24.183 --> 11:25.267
Thanks again, Yota!

11:26.310 --> 11:27.436
Hey! See you tomorrow?

11:28.562 --> 11:29.522
Yep, I'll be there.

11:30.022 --> 11:31.524
Okay, have a great night.

11:32.149 --> 11:32.983
Yeah, see ya!

11:35.319 --> 11:36.237
See ya tomorrow.

11:46.288 --> 11:47.123
Hmm

11:52.670 --> 11:53.546
Koyuki...

11:54.088 --> 11:54.964
Hikawa...

11:58.300 --> 12:00.136
Has she... always gone here?

12:00.636 --> 12:02.596
I think her last name's Hikawa.

12:02.680 --> 12:03.681
She's in class two.

12:04.265 --> 12:06.600
I heard she's a loner, and super
unfriendly.

12:13.232 --> 12:16.026
Class two was the quiet class, if I
remember correctly.

12:17.528 --> 12:20.990
Maybe she just hasn't found anyone
else that she vibes with yet.

12:22.575 --> 12:26.412
I'd always been curious about her
whenever I saw her.

12:27.663 --> 12:28.581
She's alone again.

12:32.251 --> 12:33.085
SQUISH

12:33.753 --> 12:35.171
Every time I see her...

12:36.505 --> 12:37.339
I feel...

12:38.382 --> 12:39.800
Sorry for- Hm?

12:40.426 --> 12:41.969
INCOMING CALL

12:44.305 --> 12:47.183
Hey, Minato. Sorry, but can we meet up?

12:47.850 --> 12:49.310
I wanna talk about something.

12:50.144 --> 12:51.729
Yeah. No problem.

13:08.579 --> 13:10.247
So, what do you wanna talk about?

13:14.251 --> 13:15.085
Aren't you cold?

13:22.051 --> 13:22.927
I wanna break up.

13:27.765 --> 13:29.225
What makes you say that?

13:32.144 --> 13:33.395
I can't trust you.

13:34.897 --> 13:38.234
I mean, look, you're a very nice
guy, I'll give you that, but...

13:39.068 --> 13:39.902
I don't think...

13:40.444 --> 13:43.781
I don't think you ever really liked me,
did you, Minato?

13:45.032 --> 13:47.076
Your heart was never really in it.

13:50.037 --> 13:52.623
Did I do something wrong to make you
feel that way?

13:54.041 --> 13:56.752
Stop responding to everything with a
question.

13:56.836 --> 13:57.837
You always do that.

13:58.337 --> 14:00.589
Just show me how you really feel
for once!

14:06.804 --> 14:08.222
Know what I think?

14:09.390 --> 14:11.684
You don't have a real sense of self.

14:14.895 --> 14:15.729
I'm home.

14:18.107 --> 14:19.942
Wait, what were you doing out this late?

14:20.025 --> 14:21.402
Is something the matter?

14:21.485 --> 14:22.862
Mm? Nah, don't worry.

14:23.821 --> 14:24.989
It's nothing important.

14:28.909 --> 14:29.743
Yay!

14:30.578 --> 14:32.872
I mean, shoot, oh no, that really sucks,
buddy!

14:32.955 --> 14:36.750
I just got dumped. Can you at least
pretend to feel bad for me or something?

14:36.834 --> 14:38.127
How many times is this now?

14:38.210 --> 14:40.671
Yeah, at this point it's actually kind of
funny.

14:40.754 --> 14:43.340
But I'm sure you'll find another
girlfriend soon.

14:43.424 --> 14:45.551
What? Did you get dumped again, Amamiya?

14:46.051 --> 14:47.094
That's right.

14:47.595 --> 14:51.223
I was in the middle of studying last
night, and she called and asked me to

14:51.307 --> 14:53.684
- come meet her. Then dumped me.
- Oof, brutal.

14:53.767 --> 14:56.979
I always get dumped, and I just
keep asking myself...

14:58.856 --> 15:00.357
- How come?
- Huh?

15:00.441 --> 15:01.275
Well, I, uh...

15:01.358 --> 15:03.193
HE DOES THIS IF I DON'T KEEP AN EYE ON HIM

15:03.277 --> 15:04.111
- Ugh.
- Fujita, don't let him charm you like

15:04.194 --> 15:05.070
that! You can't look this guy in the eye
for more than three seconds!

15:05.154 --> 15:07.072
BA-DUMP, BA-DUMP

15:08.824 --> 15:11.076
- I'll hold him off. Run while you still
- Morning, everyone!

15:11.160 --> 15:11.994
- Can!
- What the...

15:12.077 --> 15:14.330
Seriously, Minato?
What have you done this time?

15:14.413 --> 15:16.165
- Jeez.
- I didn't do anything.

15:16.248 --> 15:18.000
Why do you assume that every time?

15:19.209 --> 15:20.836
Oh. That's right.

15:23.797 --> 15:24.632
Hm...

15:28.093 --> 15:31.513
I'm telling you, the school store's
a treasure trove if you go early.

15:31.597 --> 15:33.515
- Hey, Yota.
- Hm?

15:33.599 --> 15:36.310
Did I happen to see you walking
Hikawa home yesterday?

15:37.102 --> 15:38.604
I know what he'll say...

15:38.687 --> 15:40.648
Huh? No way, you've got it all wrong.

15:40.731 --> 15:41.941
It's not like that.

15:42.983 --> 15:44.109
- Oh, you saw us.
- Huh?

15:44.193 --> 15:45.027
Hm?

15:46.195 --> 15:49.365
We just happened to run into each other,
so we walked together.

15:52.576 --> 15:54.828
Oh, okay. So that's all?

15:55.329 --> 15:57.289
Just saying, 'cause you kinda...

16:01.126 --> 16:02.628
SCHOOL NURSE'S OFFICE

16:02.711 --> 16:03.545
Oh.

16:04.213 --> 16:07.174
Hey, Hikawa!
Why are you in the nurse's office?

16:07.257 --> 16:09.134
- Are you sick or hurt of something?
- Um.

16:09.218 --> 16:10.260
No, I just, I, um...

16:11.345 --> 16:12.513
Huh? Hey, what is it?

16:13.722 --> 16:14.765
Oh, Yota, hi.

16:15.933 --> 16:16.892
First name basis?

16:17.685 --> 16:18.894
Hey there, Koyun!

16:20.062 --> 16:20.896
Him too?

16:21.605 --> 16:22.648
Not feeling that well?

16:22.731 --> 16:23.691
Are you okay?

16:24.191 --> 16:26.777
Oh, I'm fine.
I'm just here to get close to the heater.

16:26.860 --> 16:29.655
But why's that? Do you think it's
that cold out today?

16:29.738 --> 16:31.907
You seen the weather? It's freezing.

16:31.991 --> 16:33.158
Got your contacts in?

16:33.242 --> 16:34.576
Jeez, it's like I don't even exist.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.578
- Yeah! I can see perfectly.
- Oh, good.

16:36.662 --> 16:37.538
Hey, Miss Hikawa.

16:38.038 --> 16:38.956
Oh!

16:39.039 --> 16:41.125
You're letting all of the precious heat
out.

16:41.208 --> 16:43.335
So, if you're going, would you close the
door?

16:43.419 --> 16:44.253
Go on, shoo!

16:45.004 --> 16:46.547
She got pretty mad at you there.

16:46.630 --> 16:48.173
Noriko is always like that.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.634
Hikawa, you going to the fourth floor?

16:52.011 --> 16:53.303
We're going upstairs too.

16:53.971 --> 16:54.972
Well, I...

16:56.015 --> 16:58.308
Gotta go to the first floor to, um...
my locker.

16:58.392 --> 16:59.226
My locker.

17:00.019 --> 17:00.853
Gotcha.

17:00.936 --> 17:02.104
BRISKLY

17:02.187 --> 17:04.565
- Well then, I'll just, uh...
- See ya in a bit!

17:06.108 --> 17:06.942
In a bit?

17:16.201 --> 17:18.871
Did they really "just happen" to run into
each other?

17:20.789 --> 17:23.959
Woo! I studied my butt off today!

17:24.043 --> 17:26.086
Then again, I always do.

17:26.170 --> 17:29.798
But to be honest, there're things I
still don't get, and sometimes I

17:29.882 --> 17:32.926
wanna talk things out and ask questions
while we're studying.

17:33.010 --> 17:35.679
Then after school tomorrow, wanna just
study in the classroom?

17:35.763 --> 17:37.347
I can help explain stuff.

17:37.431 --> 17:38.807
You're cool with that?

17:38.891 --> 17:41.769
Please! Share all your wisdom and smarts
with me, Sensei!

17:41.852 --> 17:43.645
Well, I don't know about all that.

17:43.729 --> 17:44.813
BAM

17:44.897 --> 17:46.607
Sensei! Oh no!

17:46.690 --> 17:47.608
Owie.

17:47.691 --> 17:48.692
Uh...

17:48.776 --> 17:50.611
Jeez, that looks like it hurt. You
alright?

17:50.694 --> 17:53.072
Eh, I bump my head into things all
the time.

17:54.531 --> 17:56.867
- Oh.
- Oy, Yota's class...

17:58.327 --> 17:59.745
Seems like it'll be noisy.

18:00.704 --> 18:02.289
- Hm.
- Don't worry.

18:02.372 --> 18:03.207
Huh?

18:03.290 --> 18:05.542
When the bell rings, the noisy ones all
leave.

18:05.626 --> 18:07.169
Yeah, they all go home.

18:07.252 --> 18:08.087
He just read my mind.

18:08.170 --> 18:09.004
I KIND OF LIKE IT

18:09.088 --> 18:09.379
Noise isn't really Koyun's vibe.

18:09.463 --> 18:10.547
How embarrassing.

18:14.009 --> 18:15.594
SPACE FOR ONE PERSON

18:16.095 --> 18:17.221
Huh.

18:20.015 --> 18:21.183
Let's play for it.

18:21.850 --> 18:23.685
- Rock, paper, sci-
- Rock, paper, sci-

18:23.769 --> 18:24.603
- Oh!
- Oh!

18:24.686 --> 18:25.646
- Go ahead, Sir!
- Go ahead, Sir!

18:25.729 --> 18:26.563
No, please sit.

18:26.647 --> 18:28.607
- I insist.
- No, it's okay. Take it.

18:28.690 --> 18:31.527
- PR face.
- We're getting off at the next station.

18:31.610 --> 18:32.444
What?

18:33.737 --> 18:37.699
Please use the stairs in the middle of
the platform to transfer to other lines.

18:39.201 --> 18:42.454
- Oh no! Hurry! Oh no, oh no, oh no, oh no,
- The doors on platform three are closing.

18:42.538 --> 18:43.372
Oh no!

18:48.085 --> 18:50.212
HUFF, HUFF

18:50.295 --> 18:53.215
- You could've just let him have it.
- I dunno, it just came out.

18:53.298 --> 18:54.758
Why did you have to lie to the man?!

18:54.842 --> 18:55.676
I was embarrassed!

18:55.759 --> 18:56.635
FOGGY

18:57.136 --> 19:00.556
Speaking of embarrassing, my heavy
breathing's fogged up the window.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.981
Oh no, you're making me laugh too!

19:12.526 --> 19:16.488
After finals, I'm back to working after
school, which means we won't be able to

19:16.572 --> 19:17.406
THEY TEND TO TALK A LITTLE MORE WHEN

19:17.489 --> 19:18.323
walk home together. walk home together.

19:18.407 --> 19:19.950
THEY ARE ABOUT TO SAY GOODBYE

19:20.033 --> 19:22.369
- Huh?
- You've never been right?

19:22.452 --> 19:24.163
I'll throw in a free smile for ya!

19:26.165 --> 19:26.999
Hmm.

19:28.083 --> 19:30.669
- Stylish burger! Yay!
- Honestly, I'm a bit intimidated

19:30.752 --> 19:32.421
by the idea of going there alone.

19:32.504 --> 19:34.423
BECAUSE I'M ONLY A HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT

19:34.506 --> 19:36.049
Their burgers are crazy expensive.

19:36.133 --> 19:38.635
If I ask the manager, he might give you a
discount!

19:38.719 --> 19:40.262
Sure, I'll knock some Yen off for ya.

19:40.345 --> 19:41.388
SHOP MANAGER

19:41.889 --> 19:44.683
If you're scared to go alone, you can
just drag Yota along?

19:44.766 --> 19:45.767
Mm.

19:45.851 --> 19:47.978
Wait, no, Yota has his after school club.

19:48.061 --> 19:49.104
Hm.

19:51.982 --> 19:53.066
Well, see ya later!

19:53.150 --> 19:56.069
- ROOM 201 HIKAWA
- See you later.

20:13.921 --> 20:14.755
Oh.

20:15.339 --> 20:16.298
The laundry.

20:27.893 --> 20:31.438
- Hm?
- Was I... smiling just now?

20:33.774 --> 20:34.608
Wait.

20:35.567 --> 20:39.404
I feel a lingering happiness from today,
and I'm actually looking forward to

20:39.488 --> 20:40.614
tomorrow.

20:42.908 --> 20:44.159
It's easier to be alone.

20:44.660 --> 20:45.494
I'm having fun.

20:45.994 --> 20:47.204
I don't want to get attached.

20:47.287 --> 20:48.789
I wanna see them again.

20:48.872 --> 20:50.165
I want to be left alone.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.625
I'm excited for tomorrow.

20:54.086 --> 20:57.130
I feel all of these feelings... and all
so deeply.

20:57.965 --> 20:58.966
But they conflict.

21:01.093 --> 21:03.804
So then... what is it I really want?

21:06.139 --> 21:08.558
I have no idea what I'm feeling.

21:13.105 --> 21:14.523
GRADE 1 CLASS 6

21:14.606 --> 21:16.566
- Did you get the homework at all? I was
- Sneak peak.

21:16.650 --> 21:19.069
Completely lost. I literally had to ask
my sister to explain it to me.

21:19.152 --> 21:20.028
Glad you made it.

21:20.112 --> 21:22.364
- Ha, yeah I know. I was so embarrassed,
- Hi. Good morning.

21:22.447 --> 21:24.116
She'll never let me live it down.

21:24.950 --> 21:26.910
Miki just said she's running behind.

21:27.828 --> 21:29.621
Oh, she texted me about it too.

21:30.664 --> 21:33.041
Class five's homeroom tends to run long.

21:33.667 --> 21:36.336
Hey, why don't I just create a new group
chat for us?

21:36.420 --> 21:37.504
Oh. Smart.

21:38.255 --> 21:40.924
- Wow.
- Oh, Minato. What's up?

21:41.842 --> 21:42.676
So are you two...

21:43.802 --> 21:44.720
Like, an item?

21:44.803 --> 21:45.929
Huh? What? No!

21:46.013 --> 21:47.014
We're not! No!

21:47.681 --> 21:49.599
Miki's gonna be joining us here soon.

21:49.683 --> 21:50.600
Miki too?

21:51.101 --> 21:52.644
That's such a random group.

21:52.728 --> 21:53.812
CLATTER

21:53.895 --> 21:55.772
Huh? W- wait, Minato?!

21:56.315 --> 21:58.567
Do you not want me to be here or
something?

21:58.650 --> 22:00.444
No, it's not that at all.

22:01.361 --> 22:03.071
Miki's acting more like herself.

22:05.824 --> 22:07.826
So... are you all studying together?

22:07.909 --> 22:09.328
That's right, you got it!

22:09.411 --> 22:10.370
I see.

22:16.168 --> 22:17.002
Sounds fun.

22:17.711 --> 22:18.795
Let's get to it!

22:23.133 --> 22:23.967
Huh?
